Principal Component Analysis (PCA) was used to check overall variation among samples including differences in morphometrics among species, being an input to multiple regressions. Analyses were made using all measurements listed above except for the caudal fin length, which is broken in several specimens. PCA on covariances of base 14 logarithmically transformed measurements were obtained using Past version 1.28 2004 (
Ryan et al ., 1995
), being the first component (PC 1 ) removed from the analysis.

