)

Coloration in alcohol (
Fig. 10
): ground color yellowish, with chromatophores on posterior margin of the scales forming three irregular series of spots along the flanks; row of slender dark brown markings along belly, a vertical row of small dark spots from hind border of eye to chin and other from anterior margin of eye to upper jaw; small black dots on opercle; fins with inconspicuous series of dark brown spots along the rays; eyeball black or silvery on lower half and dark on the upper one; iris black.

